entities.KoseiHelper/ClimbJumpController.attributes.description.checkWallBoostDirection=wip
entities.KoseiHelper/ClimbJumpController.attributes.description.dustType=The type of particles that should appear on the wall when climbjumping.\nNot to be confused with the player sweat.
entities.KoseiHelper/ClimbJumpController.attributes.description.climbJumpSound=The sounds that a climbjump makes.\n"event:/char/madeline/jump_climb_left" and "event:/char/madeline/jump_climb_right" are the two vanilla events.\nThis field does not need the "left" and "right" suffixes.
entities.KoseiHelper/ClimbJumpController.attributes.description.wallBoostStaminaRefund=How much stamina the player would get back after performing a wallboost.\nRead the wallboost timer tooltip for a wallboost explanation.\nValues >27.5 will make the player unable to regain stamina if they have more than 110 minus this value.\nFor example, setting the refund to 50 means that stamina will be refunded from a wallboost if it is below 60.
entities.KoseiHelper/ClimbJumpController.attributes.description.horizontalSpeedMultiplier=Multiplies the horizontal speed that climbjumps give (while a direction is being held).\nIt also affects speed in techs derived from climbjumps, like cornerboosts.
entities.KoseiHelper/ClimbJumpController.attributes.description.sweat=Whether the player should sweat when performing a climbjump.\nNot to be confused with the smaller sweat from climbing.
entities.KoseiHelper/ClimbJumpController.attributes.description.speedMultiplierCase=Whether the speed multiplier should affect climbjumps/cornerboosts while a horizontal input is being pressed/not pressed/always.\nE.g.: a multiplier of -1 with "OnlyNeutrals" will produce reverse cornerboosts if not holding left/right, and normal cornerboosts if holding left/right.

